intro: Cryptocarya calandoi, commonly known as the Calandoi laurel, is a species of flowering plant in the family Lauraceae. It is native to the tropical rainforests of northern Queensland, Australia. The plant is characterized by its dark green, glossy leaves and small, fragrant white flowers that appear in clusters. It produces small, berry-like fruits that are edible but not commonly consumed by humans. Cryptocarya calandoi plays a role in its ecosystem as a food source for various native animals and insects.
